volunteer_experiences.description:
Support marketing activities of the RUG towards prospective international students through online testimonials and social media presence;
Be an advisor and contact point of the RUG by providing country expertise advice to the marketing department;
Be an advisor and contact point of the RUG for potential international students;
Attended workshops in Professional Communication and Networking & Pitching.

Guarantee and improve the quality of the BA by:
Consenting, consulting and assessing the implementation and elements of the Teaching and Examination Regulations of the BA;
Issue solicited and unsolicited recommendations and proposals to the degree programme boards regarding various teaching matters relevant for the BA.
Monitor the quality of the BA by:
Constantly communicating to peers the outcomes of the Programme Committee meetings and receiving feedback on the quality of study and expectations for the future;  
Evaluating and discussing student evaluations regarding the teaching and quality of courses;
Formulating quality improvement proposals.

Organize and attend Stenden Toastmasters meetings and events;
Keep records on members’ development and course achievements;
Ensure members’ satisfaction;
Provide personal coaching on achieving goals in public speaking and leadership skills.

Support and represent Stenden Hogeschool in a variety of marketing activities, such as:
Being a contact person during International Open Days;
Increasing Stenden’s visibility by participating in local and international events and university presentations;
Deliver presentations to potential students; 
Provide university tours to individual or groups of potential students.
